title: CRC_celecoxib_M4858
biomaterial_provider_ch1: Siteman Cancer Center Multiplex Gene Expression Core (St. Louis, MO)
treatment_protocol_ch1: Patients undergoing surgical resection of histologically proven primary colorectal adenocarcinomas were consented for participation in the study.  The patients enrolled in this study were randomized to receive either 400 mg celecoxib two times per day (n=11) or no COX-2 inhibitor (n=12) for 7 days prior to surgical resection.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated from surgically resected, histologically confirmed colorectal primary adenocarcinomas using a TRIzol RNA isolation kit (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer’s recommended protocol at the Siteman Cancer Center Tissue Procurement Core (St. Louis, MO).
data_processing: Affymetrix .cel files were imported into GeneSpring GX 7.3 using GC-RMA File Preprocessor.  Data was normalized by (1) setting all expression measurements <0.01 to 0.01, (2) a per chip normalization to the 50th percentile, and (3) a per gene normalization to the median value across all chips.
contact_department: Institute for Pharmacogenomics and Individualized Therapy
contact_institute: University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill
